value.title: Biden closes out his campaign in Pennsylvania, promising 'the beginning of a new day'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden closed his presidential campaign Monday night in Pennsylvania, lambasting President Donald Trump's handling of the coronavirus pandemic and promising to unite a country in crisis if he wins Tuesday.

value.title: In final rally, Kamala Harris urges Pennsylvania to use 'power' and vote
value.excerpt: In her final campaign rally before Election Day, Kamala Harris urged Pennsylvania to get out and vote. Harris said, “Your vote is your voice and your voice is your power.”

value.title: The Point: Marco Rubio goes full Trump on election eve
value.excerpt: Even as some ambitious 2024 Republicans have begun to distance themselves from Donald Trump's version of, uh, conservatism, Florida's Sen. Marco Rubio offered the equivalent of a bear hug for the incumbent just 48 hours before Election Day.

value.title: Bolton: Trump trying to set up con on his own supporters
value.excerpt: CNN's Jake Tapper speaks with former national security adviser John Bolton about President Donald Trump's rhetoric around when mail-in ballots should be counted and Trump's threats of legal action after polls close on Election Day.

value.title: Trump and Biden race to shore up votes in final hours before Election Day
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden are racing to drive out the votes of Americans not among the more than 91 million who already cast early ballots as an election that started months before the pandemic, and then was defined by it, heads into its final, frantic hours.

value.title: In Miami, coalition of Latino evangelical leaders endorses Biden
value.excerpt: One pastor said that although the coalition is a nonprofit and nonpartisan, “in moments of crisis, the church has to unite the people.”

value.title: NFL legend Brett Favre endorses Trump for president
value.excerpt: NFL great Brett Favre has endorsed President Donald Trump for reelection. He's one of the most prominent figures in sports to publicly pledge support for the President.

value.title: ‘People Are Going To Be Shocked’: Return of the ‘Shy’ Trump Voter?
value.excerpt: In 2016, pollsters Arie Kapteyn and Robert Cahaly saw Trump coming. In 2020, they see polls again underestimating his support.

value.title: Biden and Cunningham Hold Slim Leads in North Carolina, Poll Finds
value.excerpt: Joe Biden and Cal Cunningham both led their Republican rivals by three points, a Times/Siena College survey found. Perhaps most notably, 64 percent of respondents said they had already voted.

value.title: Top Democrat says Trump administration moving ahead with sale of F-35 jets to the UAE
value.excerpt: The chairman of the House Foreign Affairs Committee said Thursday that the Trump administration has informally notified Congress of its intent to move forward with a major arms sale to the United Arab Emirates involving advanced F-35 jets.

value.title: Trump is taking credit for the 'biggest and best' GDP  in American history. Here are the facts
value.excerpt: The US government just published an eye-popping report: Gross domestic product, the broadest measure of the country's economic growth, grew at a stunning 33.1% annual rate in the third quarter.

value.title: Watch: Trump rushes Sen. Martha McSally on stage during Arizona rally
value.excerpt: During a campaign rally in Goodyear, Ariz., President Donald Trump rushed Republican Senator Martha McSally on stage to speak. McSally is in a close Senate race with her Democratic challenger astronaut Mark Kelly.

value.title: They call themselves 'Wives of the Deplorables' because their husbands support Trump
value.excerpt: Carole Catherine did not know her husband, Tim, supported Donald Trump until the day after Hillary Clinton lost the 2016 election. She called him the next morning crying.

value.title: Trump uses outdated thinking in attempt to woo suburban women: I'm 'getting your husbands back to work'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump offered his latest appeal to suburban women Tuesday evening, promising to get their husbands "back to work" if he's reelected.

value.title: Trump appears to give a pass to the domestic kidnapping plot against Whitmer
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump repeatedly attacked Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer, a Democrat, during his rally in Lansing, Michigan, on Tuesday, at one point taking credit for the FBI thwarting a plot to kidnap her and then immediately downplaying the actual threat that had been posed to Whitmer.

value.title: Fact check: Trump falsely claims Pennsylvanians 'can't go to church'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump keeps falsely declaring that various states run by Democratic governors are "closed" or "shut down."

value.title: Pence's office says he did not attend swearing-in due to CDC guidelines
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence did not attend Monday night's White House swearing-in ceremony for Supreme Court Justice Amy Coney Barrett because he was adhering to US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention guidelines to prevent the spread of the coronavirus, an administration official told CNN.

value.title: Twitter labels Trump post about mail ballots as ‘disputed’ and ‘misleading’
value.excerpt: The president claimed, without evidence, there were “problems and discrepancies” with mail-in ballots “all over the USA.”

value.title: Judge rejects DOJ's attempt to defend Trump in E. Jean Carroll rape defamation lawsuit
value.excerpt: A federal judge on Tuesday denied the Justice Department's effort to intervene in a defamation lawsuit brought against President Donald Trump by a longtime magazine columnist who has alleged he raped her, paving the way for the case to proceed.

value.title: Stephen Colbert: Mike Pence Is ‘America’s Spare Tire’
value.excerpt: After the White House called the vice president an essential worker, Colbert said: “At best, he is vice essential. You want him in the trunk, but you hope to never have to use him.”

value.title: Ivanka Trump, Jared Kushner threaten to sue over billboard
value.excerpt: Ivanka Trump and Jared Kushner are threatening to sue The Lincoln Project over billboards the organization erected in New York City's Times Square. CNN's Brianna Keilar and Alexandra Field report.

value.title: Kayleigh McEnany once praised Biden as a 'man of the people' who resonates with "middle class" over 'tycoon' Trump
value.excerpt: Prior to becoming a prominent backer of Donald Trump, Kayleigh McEnany praised then-Vice President Joe Biden as "funny and likable" and a "man of the people" who resonates with "middle class voters."

value.title: Pence skips public health recommended self-quarantine but does change plans after staff outbreak
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence, despite flouting public health guidelines by still campaigning after being exposed to people testing positive with coronavirus, is taking some precautions on the road.

value.excerpt: EDITOR'S NOTE: This story was reported by the Center for Responsive Politics and CNN.
